# Spring Basic App

A beginner-friendly Spring Framework project created as part of my Java Full Stack Deep Skilling program.

##  Exercises Covered

###  Exercise 1: Configuring a Basic Spring Application
- Created a Maven project
- Added Spring Context dependency
- Configured Spring using `applicationContext.xml`
- Created and managed Spring Beans
- Loaded the Spring IoC Container
- Retrieved beans using `ApplicationContext`

###  Exercise 2: Implementing Dependency Injection
- Implemented Dependency Injection (DI)
- Injected dependencies using XML configuration
- Understood Inversion of Control (IoC)
- Reduced object coupling using Spring

###  Exercise 4: Creating and Configuring a Maven Project
- Created a Maven project
- Configured `pom.xml`
- Added Spring dependencies
- Understood Maven project structure
- Built and ran the project successfully

##  Technologies Used

- Java 21
- Spring Framework 6
- Maven
- IntelliJ IDEA

